# SSH to Raspberry Pi: Use Desktop Commander

When connecting to Raspberry Pi kiosks via SSH, **ALWAYS use the MCP Desktop Commander tool** (`user-desktop-commander-start_process`), not standard Shell commands.

## Why Desktop Commander?

- ✅ Proper handling of interactive SSH sessions
- ✅ Better output capture and monitoring
- ✅ Supports password-based authentication with plink
- ✅ Manages persistent connections for fleet operations

## Correct Approach

```typescript
// Use Desktop Commander start_process
user-desktop-commander-start_process({
  command: "plink -ssh pi@192.168.1.100 -pw raspberry 'ls -la /home/pi'",
  timeout_ms: 10000
})
```

## What NOT to Do

```bash
# ❌ DON'T use Shell tool for SSH
ssh pi@192.168.1.100
```

## Related

For comprehensive Pi SSH operations, use the **ssh-fleet-manager** skill which provides full fleet management capabilities with Desktop Commander.
